<hl>
<seg id=1> Retailing Index in August Went Down by 8.3%, Compared With that of Last Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retailing index in August has gone down by 8.3%, compared with that of the same period in last year. This has been the continual drop of this index in the 12th month. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September of 1997, the retailing index, compared with that of the same month in the year before, has always been falling down without going up, indicating that the domestic retailing business is still struggling at the low tide. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Compared with that of July this year, the retailing index has also fallen down by 8.3%. </seg>
<seg id=5> If excluding the car sales, the index would fall down by 3.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The figure released by the Statistics Bureau shows that in August almost all the retailing activities are slump. </seg>
<seg id=7> The car sales in July went up rapidly by 41.4%, but in August, it has gone down by 19.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Other retailing trades, whose businesses went down, include furniture and household goods (8%), textile and private necessities (7.8%), department store and supermarket (2.6%), gas station (1.3%) and grocerystore(0.3%). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> On the other hand, food and drink industry index in August has gone down by 4.5%, compared with that of the same period in last year, which has been the drop in the 7th month continuously since February of 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> But, if compared with that of July, food and drink industry index has slightly gone up by 1.4%. </seg>
<seg id=11> The money people spent on food and drinks have increased from 0.245 billion yuan in July to 0.248 billion yuan in August. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The relevant growth rate is mainly driven by the increase of 6.6% in the turnover of the fast food restaurants. </seg>
<seg id=13> The business of food and drinks, except for the restaurants, has also increased by 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> The retailing index and the food and drinks industry index are figures monthly released by the Statistics Bureau, which are especially designed to look into the short-term situation of retailing industry and food and drinks industry in our country. </seg>
</p>
